# Edward Graff

}}
Edward Graff (August 20, 1897 &ndash; March 19, 1954) was an American rugby union player who competed in the 1924 Summer Olympics. He was born in San Francisco, California. Graff was a member of the American rugby union team, which won the gold medal.
